  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>NHS Business Definition: National Contact Point - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>

  <p>
The 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_national_contact_point">National Contact Point</xref>
 is an 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_organisation">ORGANISATION</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
The 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_national_contact_point">National Contact Point</xref>
 (
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_national_contact_point">NCP</xref>
) is run by 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_nhs_england">NHS England</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
The primary role of the 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_national_contact_point">National Contact Point</xref>
 is the provision of information to prospective European 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENTS</xref>
 travelling to England for treatment ('incoming 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENTS</xref>
') and English residents seeking funding for healthcare in the 
    <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_definitions/european_economic_area.asp"
            scope="external"
            format="html">European_Economic_Area</xref>
 ('outgoing 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENTS</xref>
').  </p>
  <p>
For further information on the role of the 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_national_contact_point">National Contact Point</xref>
, see the NHS website at: 
    <xref href="https://www.nhs.uk/NHSEngland/Healthcareabroad/national-contact-point/Pages/uk-national-contact-point.aspx"
            scope="external"
            format="html">National Contact Points for the United Kingdom</xref>
.  </p>

